<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1267,1473]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1902" box="[276,405,1267,1293]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,405,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Melanomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises six species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tomes 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[672,1005,1267,1294]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caliginosus">
<emphasis box="[672,838,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. caliginosus</emphasis>
(Tomes 1860)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goldman 1918)" baseAuthorityName="Goldman" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1018,1393,1267,1293]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysomelas">
<emphasis box="[1018,1196,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. chrysomelas</emphasis>
(Goldman 1918)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Allen 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. columbianus</emphasis>
(Allen 1899)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goldman 1918)" baseAuthorityName="Goldman" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[463,786,1303,1329]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idoneus">
<emphasis box="[463,588,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. idoneus</emphasis>
(Goldman 1918)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[799,1138,1303,1329]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustulus">
<emphasis box="[799,954,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. robustulus</emphasis>
(Thomas 1914)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sanborn 1949)" baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zunigae">
<emphasis box="[1200,1325,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. zunigae</emphasis>
(Sanborn 1949)
</taxonomicName>
. The species of the genus were found in lowland or lower montane forested habitats in Central America from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,260,1375,1401]" name="Honduras" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Honduras</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[301,393,1375,1401]" name="Panama" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Panama</collectingCountry>
, and south to north-western South America, in 
<collectingCountry box="[941,1054,1375,1401]" name="Colombia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1163,1375,1401]" name="Ecuador" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1177,1231,1375,1401]" name="Peru" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and westernmost 
<collectingCountry box="[151,266,1411,1437]" name="Venezuela" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D." box="[281,565,1410,1437]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="894 - 1531" refId="ref69694" refString="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D. (2005) Superfamily Muroidea. In: Wilson, D. &amp; Reeder, D. (Eds.), Mammal Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference, 3 rd ed. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 894 - 1531." type="book chapter" year="2005">Musser &amp; Carleton 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hanson, J. D. &amp; Bradley, R. D." box="[578,855,1411,1437]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref67924" refString="Hanson, J. D. &amp; Bradley, R. D. (2008) Molecular diversity within Melanomys caliginosus (Rodentia: Oryzomyini): evidence for multiple species. Occasional papers / The Museum, Texas Tech University, 275, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="2008">Hanson &amp; Bradley 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[867,1164,1411,1437]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref72147" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2013) Geographic distribution of the genera of the tribe Oryzomyini (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae) in South America: patterns of distribution and diversity. Archivos de Zoologia, 44 (1), 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 44 i 1 p 1 - 120" type="journal article" year="2013">Prado &amp; Percequillo 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Loss, S." box="[1176,1425,1410,1437]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="348 - 354" refId="ref75787" refString="Weksler, M. &amp; Loss, S. (2015) Genus Melanomys Thomas, 1902. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 348 - 354." type="book chapter" year="2015">Weksler &amp; LÃ³ss 2015</bibRefCitation>
). There was cytogenetic information available only for two species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[898,1063,1447,1473]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caliginosus">
<emphasis box="[898,1063,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. caliginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Goldman" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1117,1294,1447,1473]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Melanomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysomelas">
<emphasis box="[1117,1294,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">M. chrysomelas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
